<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Basic_geometry_arm
   <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm">
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm.Curve">
A <b>Curve</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>. A 
<b>Curve</b> may be a <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Closed_curve"/>, 
or additionally may be a <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Composite_curve"/> 
or additionally may be a <express_ref linkend="Basic_curve:arm:Basic_curve_arm.Trimmed_curve"/>. 
A <b>Curve</b> is the path of a point moving through its three-dimensional 
coordinate space or of a point moving through its two-dimensional coordinate space. A <b>Curve</b> shall be arc-wise connected. A <b>Curve</b> shall have an arc length greater than 
zero.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Basic_geometry_arm  Entity: Line  
   <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Line"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm.Line">
	A <b>Line</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> that  is straight. A <b>Line</b> is considered infinite.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Basic_geometry_arm  Entity: Plane  
   <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Plane"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm.Plane">
	A <b>Plane</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Surface"/>
that is flat. Planes are considered as infinite.
 
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Basic_geometry_arm  Entity: Point_on_curve  
   <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Point_on_curve"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm.Point_on_curve">
	A <b>Point_on_curve</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>

 that characterizes a point which lies on a curve.
It results from the evaluation of the function that defines the <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/> with a particular parameter.
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm.Point_on_curve.supporting_curve">
 the <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Curve"/>

 onto which the point is evaluated.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Basic_geometry_arm  Entity: Point_on_surface  
   <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Point_on_surface"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm.Point_on_surface">
	A <b>Point_on_surface</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>

 that characterizes a point that lies on a parametric surface.
It either results from the evaluation of the function that defines the <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Surface"/>

 with a particular couple of parameters or from the evaluation of a point where a curve on the surface collapses.
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm.Point_on_surface.supporting_surface">
 the <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Surface"/> on 
which the point lies.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Basic_geometry_arm  Entity: Surface  
   <express_ref linkend="basic_geometry:arm:Basic_geometry_arm.Surface"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Basic_geometry_arm.Surface">
	A <b>Surface</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>

 that is a  continuous 2D subspace of a 3D space. 
<note number="1">A <b>Surface</b> may not be manifold.</note>
	<note number="2">
	The <b>Surface</b> entity is a supertype of various specific kinds of surfaces. The definition of these specific types is outside the scope of the present module.</note>
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
